description:
Welcome to the Jenna & Julien Podcast where we talk about all the things. If you are looking for your everyday, normal, by the book podcast, then you're in the wrong place. We created this because we tend to have awesome, random, and sometimes drunk conversations that we realized had to be shared with the lovely internet world. So here we are. 

We also like to ustream during the podcast to get some live interaction and also quick on-the-spot input on our chats--you can participate here: http://www.ustream.tv/channel/jsolo123

Subscribe to this channel for new podcasts EVERY MONDAY

iTunes: http://itunes.com/jennajulienpodcast

SoundCloud: http://soundcloud.com/JennaJulienPodcast

You can follow us on all the things:
Instagram: http://instagram.com/jennajulienpod
Twitter: https://twitter.com/jennajulienpod
YouTube: http://youtube.com/JennaJulienPodcast

episodes.title: Podcast #126 - Ban Roulette
episodes.description:
Quick note: We’d like to reiterate that this podcast was made as a lighthearted joke that anyone could laugh at and enjoy. We made up fictitious bans that a fictitious president was trying to enforce, all more ridiculous than the next. And our arguing for which law should stay versus which should go was purely entertaining the nature of the game and not based on any beliefs that we actually hold. We are very aware how difficult this weekend was for a LOT of people and very much hope you understand that we take it seriously. Humor for us is a familiar tactic we call on to deal with tough situations and that’s what this episode was for us. We love all of you and hope you got something positive from this week’s podcast game. See you next week. Dink.

This episode was riddled with passion. For me (Julien), I brought up the issue in light of the recent video that surfaced of Jon Jones threatening to kill Daniel Cormier, of the limits of trash talking in the UFC. The uncomfortable feeling you get from certain people on the internet, that compels you click that dreaded unfollow button..yeah we talked all about that. Then we discussed what it's like when friends who get involved in pyramid schemes might as well not be the same person you used to be friends with anymore.
